{
  "texts": [
    "Rather, TMT AI literacy seems to affect HR-related AI implementation ability directly and indirectly through AI orientation.",
    "As such, this partial mediation also supports the claims made above and potential explanations mentioned in prior literature that executives directly affect implementation ability, for example, through hiring policies (Rana & Sharma, 2019).",
    "Lastly, we found that firm type moderates TMT AI literacy's effect on HR-related AI implementation ability, such that the effect is stronger in startup firms than incumbent firms.",
    "In contrast, we did not find any support for a moderation effect of firm type on TMT AI literacy's effect on AI orientation.",
    "In the context of firm types representing different organizational resource configurations (Andries et al., 2013; Baker & Nelson, 2005), prior research has shown that these configurations seem to differ in their ability to adopt AI (Oehmichen et al., 2023) and how they support executives to achieve their goals."
  ]
}